1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,880
But through all his interrogations, all he discovered was that Christians were having a meal,

2
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:09,280
which they called a Thanksgiving meal, which also involved a ritual with bread and wine,

3
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:14,480
which they called the body and the blood of Jesus. So no children hiding in the bread?

4
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:19,840
Not at all. In fact, Christians were known to rescue and raise abandoned Roman babies,

5
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:24,000
as they rejected the Roman practice of killing or abandoning unwanted children.

6
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:28,240
The way Christians lived flowed from what they were taught in their meetings.

7
00:00:28,240 --> 00:00:33,440
They went around talking about a loving God who loved the world and demanded love between people,

8
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:38,560
even between enemies. In their meetings, they were taught to reject magic and violence,

9
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:42,400
and they were known for caring for the sick, as well as their very restrained,

10
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:47,520
sexual ethic. All this was highly counter-cultural in Roman society. Roman authors,

11
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:53,280
like the philosopher Galen and the satirist Lucian, both pitted and admired Christians for how they

12
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:59,200
really lived out these ideals. All this made Christians seem like a scary and a mysterious community,

